genresAdvancedInfo.name: musica morelense
genresAdvancedInfo.description: This music genre is native to the state of Morelos in Mexico and is characterized by its use of brass instruments such as the trombone, trumpet, and saxophone. The rhythms are lively and upbeat, often accompanied by dance. The lyrics often talk about the history and culture of the region, as well as social and political issues.
